Question: How to use AsyncTask in Android to read data from server:
Answer:<<<api>>>: AsyncTask
<<<code>>>: private class ReadTask extends AsyncTask<Void, Void, Void> {
    protected Void doInBackground(Void... params) {
        try {
            // your code to read from server goes here
        } catch (Exception e) {
            // handle exception
        }
        return null;
    }

    protected void onPostExecute(Void result) {
        // your code to update UI goes here
    }
}

To start the task, you can call: new ReadTask().execute();
<<<explanation>>>: Use AsyncTask to perform background operations and publish results on the UI thread without having to manipulate threads and handlers. This can make your code easier to write and read.
